        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer383727882" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8985667903310540605">I first heard of this work when I watched the movie adaptation of the play. The movie follows the script very closely, a happy rarity. Years after watching the movie, it still comes to mind very vividly, the story compelling, the characters complex, the writing superb. This is not a happy story, but it is very powerful, and leaves you thinking about the topics, and &quot;what if?&quot; thoughts for weeks afterward. What I wonder most is, would the protagonist have chosen differently, if she&apos;d had access t</span>
  <span id="freeText8985667903310540605" style="display:none">I first heard of this work when I watched the movie adaptation of the play. The movie follows the script very closely, a happy rarity. Years after watching the movie, it still comes to mind very vividly, the story compelling, the characters complex, the writing superb. This is not a happy story, but it is very powerful, and leaves you thinking about the topics, and "what if?" thoughts for weeks afterward. What I wonder most is, would the protagonist have chosen differently, if she'd had access to the internet? She'd felt alone, invalidated, and she'd had such thoughts and no one to share them with, surely she would have found forums related to her medical condition, and outlets for her thoughts and interests. This is an amazing play to read, and powerful to watch. Prepare to feel very intensely emotional. I must say, I never fold towels or perform other mundane tasks without giving a thought to the main characters in this story.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8985667903310540605" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


