        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2973791882" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11116934387266216981">This is one of those titles I&apos;ve known about, read the words &quot;&apos;night Mother&quot; and had referenced, but I never got around to reading or seeing. I figured it was some kind of soppy parent-child relationship play and skipped it. <br/><br/>Holy shit, not what I expected at all. Short and to the point, this two woman show is about the daughter planning to commit suicide and getting her mother ready for it. She&apos;s got the gun, she just has to walk her mother through how to use the washing machine, when to put out</span>
  <span id="freeText11116934387266216981" style="display:none">This is one of those titles I've known about, read the words "'night Mother" and had referenced, but I never got around to reading or seeing. I figured it was some kind of soppy parent-child relationship play and skipped it. <br /><br />Holy shit, not what I expected at all. Short and to the point, this two woman show is about the daughter planning to commit suicide and getting her mother ready for it. She's got the gun, she just has to walk her mother through how to use the washing machine, when to put out the trash, when to lock the doors for the night, how to do all the thousand and one little things that her daughter already does for her. <br /><br />And amidst this, her mother argues, pleads, cajoles, threatens, and does everything she can to avoid what she knows is her daughter's last wish. <br /><br />Harrowing as fuck. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11116934387266216981" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


