<span id="freeTextContainer17630626492932393749">This play is amazingly disturbing. It makes the reader, or the audience in turmoil. They sympathize with Jessie and with her mother at the same time. Both characters are normal, everyday characters that people would meet everywhere. The good thing about this play is that Jessie had a chance to express herself. She got a chance to tell the world that&apos;s a messed up place. Jessie and Thelma are both me. They express the inner turmoil I live in. I would really like to kill myself, but at the same ti</span>
  <span id="freeText17630626492932393749" style="display:none">This play is amazingly disturbing. It makes the reader, or the audience in turmoil. They sympathize with Jessie and with her mother at the same time. Both characters are normal, everyday characters that people would meet everywhere. The good thing about this play is that Jessie had a chance to express herself. She got a chance to tell the world that's a messed up place. Jessie and Thelma are both me. They express the inner turmoil I live in. I would really like to kill myself, but at the same time, I don't want to go to hell, and I am afraid of death. <br /><br />A brilliant play!</span>
