<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer11341244918259649040">Marsha Norman is an American playwright, screenwriter, and novelist. She received the 1983 Pulitzer Prize for Drama for her play <i>&apos;night, Mother</i>. She wrote the book and lyrics for such Broadway musicals as <i>The Secret Garden</i>, for which she won a Tony Award and the Drama Desk Award for Outstanding Book of a Musical, and <i>The Red Shoes</i>, as well as the libretto for the musical <i>The Color Purple</i>.</span>
  <span id="freeText11341244918259649040" style="display:none">Marsha Norman is an American playwright, screenwriter, and novelist. She received the 1983 Pulitzer Prize for Drama for her play <i>'night, Mother</i>. She wrote the book and lyrics for such Broadway musicals as <i>The Secret Garden</i>, for which she won a Tony Award and the Drama Desk Award for Outstanding Book of a Musical, and <i>The Red Shoes</i>, as well as the libretto for the musical <i>The Color Purple</i>.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11341244918259649040" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

</div>
